last_episode_to_air.name: Ab Initio
last_episode_to_air.overview: [From the Beginning] Harrow rides the storm when a deathly ill boy at QIFM needs his help at the very moment Mila Zoric summons him to negotiate his kidnapped son's release.

name: Harrow
overview: When a dark secret from this past threatens to be exposed, unorthodox and brilliant medical examiner, Doctor Daniel Harrow, must use all his forensic skills to keep it buried forever.

episodes.name: Actus Reus
episodes.overview: [Guilty Act] Harrow is drawn into reopening a closed case after quitting his job, even as he tries to re-connect with his estranged daughter. When a body is found in the river he finds himself drawn back to the Coroner's office.

episodes.name: Ex Animo
episodes.overview: [From The Soul] While stalling the river bones investigation, Harrow digs into the case of a woman murdered with a crossbow, coming dangerously close to a thrill-kill murderer.

episodes.name: Hic Sunt Dracones
episodes.overview: [Here be Dragons] A human arm in a dead crocodile leads Harrow and Dass to Far North Queensland, battling crocs and crooks in their pursuit of the truth.

episodes.name: Finis Vitae Sed Non Amoris
episodes.overview: When a skeleton is discovered in a suburban backyard, the home owner becomes the prime murder suspect - until Harrow begins to uncover a tragic secret.

episodes.name: Non Sum Qualis Eram
episodes.overview: Ioan Gruffudd stars as a brilliant forensic pathologist in this 10-part Australian crime drama. Harrow comes to Fern's aid after she unwittingly sells deadly party drugs, leaving a young woman dead and others hospitalised.

episodes.name: Aurum Potestas Est
episodes.overview: Two young travelers are dead and Harrow suspects the involvement of a prominent international businessman - but vested bureaucratic forces confound him at every turn.

episodes.name: Pia Mater
episodes.overview: [Gentle Mother] While Harrow investigates the deaths of a mother and son in a car accident, the mystery of Robert Quinn's disappearance escalates into a homicide investigation.

episodes.name: Peccata Patrisi
episodes.overview: [Sins of the Father] Nichol's carries out surveillance on Stephanie after she leaves Quinn a threatening voicemail. Then, after the skull from the river bones body is discovered, a positive identity is finally made. Meanwhile, Harrow investigates the suspicious death of a student from his old high school.

episodes.name: Lex Talionis
episodes.overview: A suspicious death at a nursing home causes Harrow to reflect on his own crime, as the investigation into Robert Quinn's murder gains momentum.

episodes.name: Mens Rea
episodes.overview: Harrow deals with his most bizarre autopsy yet, both Dass and Simon finally close in on the truth about who killed Robert Quinn. Season Finale.

episodes.name: Abo Imo Pectore
episodes.overview: [From the Deepest Chest] Harrow recovers from a near-fatal shooting and returns immediately to work, investigating the tragic puzzle of a young mother's psychotic episode while trying to figure out who shot him.

episodes.name: Audere Est Facere
episodes.overview: [To Dare Is to Do] Harrow investigates the death of two base jumpers while Fern deals with the fallout of her arrest on serious drug allegations.

episodes.name: Malum In Se
episodes.overview: [Evil in itself] When a mummified body is found bricked up in the basement of a suburban home, Harrow and Grace set about uncovering a grim secret that has been buried for twenty years.

episodes.name: Aegri Somnia
episodes.overview: [Hallucinations] Harrow resolves to believe that Chester really is dead, and takes a case in North Queensland, while Simon launches his own investigation into Chester.

episodes.name: Ab Initio
episodes.overview: [From the Beginning] Coping with a death that strikes close to home by focusing on work, Harrow is stunned to discover a connection between this death and another deceased man on his autopsy table.

episodes.name: Locus Poenitentiae
episodes.overview: [Opportunity to Withdraw] Harrow and Fairley are sent to a double-fatality in Fairley's hometown - a trip that will test their already strained relationship.

episodes.name: Parce Sepulto
episodes.overview: [Forgive the Dead] As Harrow and Grace investigate the death of a popular health and wellness vlogger, Harrow agitates for the exhumation of Chester's remains.

episodes.name: Sub Silentio
episodes.overview: [In Silence] While Grace autopsies the body of an elderly man discovered in an Egyptian sarcophagus, Harrow finds himself in a battle for his own life.

episodes.name: Facilis Descensus
episodes.overview: [The Descent is Easy] Harrow is desperate to prove once and for all that Francis Chester is alive and trying to kill him, but with no proof, even his most-trusted friends and colleagues doubt Harrow's state of mind.

episodes.name: Pater Familias
episodes.overview: [Father of the Family] In a thrilling climax, Harrow comes face-to-face with his greatest fears as Chester initiates the endgame.

episodes.name: Mater Semper Certa Est
episodes.overview: [The Mother is Always Certain] Confronted by the loss of a son he never knew, Harrow buries himself in his work, investigating the violent stabbing of a homeless man.

episodes.name: Damnant Quod Non Intellegunt
episodes.overview: [They Condemn What They Do Not Understand] Reeling from the discovery that his son is alive, Harrow finds a welcome distraction in one of the most bizarre cases he's ever encountered: the murder of a vampire.

episodes.name: Tarde Venientibus Ossa
episodes.overview: [To the Late Are Left the Bones] Harrow proves a suburban suicide is in fact murder, uncovering one family's secrets as he is forced to hide his own.

episodes.name: Per Stirpes
episodes.overview: [Through The Roots] Harrow is reminded why he hates camping on a hiking trip with Fairley and Nichols.

episodes.name: Ut Biberent Quoniam Esse Nollent
episodes.overview: [So That They Might Drink, Since They Refused To Eat] As Harrow's attempts to reconnect with his son are frustrated, Fern and James grow closer - while the baffling deaths of two teens sharpen Harrow's concern for his own children.

episodes.name: Ne Puero Gladium
episodes.overview: [Do Not Give a Sword to a Boy] While pressure mounts on Harrow to stop defending his son James, two baffling deaths demand all his wit and courage to solve - before another life is lost.

episodes.name: Sola Dosis Facit Venemum
episodes.overview: [The Dose Makes the Poison] The mysterious death of a hotel maid draws Harrow into a dark world of espionage and assassination, while Nichols edges closer to catching Harrow's wayward son, James.

episodes.name: Alea Iacta Est
episodes.overview: [The Die Has Been Cast] After two men die in a duel, Harrow uncovers a web of Machiavellian intrigue within a suburban historical society. Tanya's return forces Harrow to reassess the last 20 years of his life.

episodes.name: Quam Innocentum Damnari
episodes.overview: [An Innocent Man Is Punished] While Harrow investigates a baffling crime involving siblings, James brings danger closer to his half-sister Fern than ever before - and pays a high price.

episodes.name: Ab Initio
episodes.overview: [From the Beginning] Harrow rides the storm when a deathly ill boy at QIFM needs his help at the very moment Mila Zoric summons him to negotiate his kidnapped son's release.
